HEADWORD: hotei-chiku
<hw>hotei-chiku</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small bamboo
(<spn>Phyllostachys aurea</spn>) of Southeast China having slender culms
flexuous when young.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fishpole bamboo, gosan-chiku, <spn>Phyllostachys
aurea</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
